description.0: The thrilling conclusion to the series! Sabretooth finally tracks down his son, but it's not the happy father-son reunion you might expect…
description.2: Last issue's lost souls are reanimated in new bodies! How will they cope?
description.5: Master Arca explains that he has been chosen as the Jedi watchman of the Onderon system, and sends Ulic, Cay and Tott to Iziz to settle this 300-year conflict known as the Beast Wars. Soon after arriving in Queen Amanoa's throne room in Iziz, several Beast Riders burst through the window and kidnap Princess Galia. Amanoa sends the Jedi out into the wildlands to save her, but their ship is shot down by the defending Beast Riders...
description.9: The Hangman has paid a big price for his power and he, along with the Lethal Legion, have targeted the Avengers West Coast for death!
description.15: The First Appearance of Daredevil's Black Armor Costume!  At last, Daredevil comes face-to-face with Eddie, and the truth about the mysterious man's past is revealed! But first, Daredevil will have his hands full with an eerily familiar creature known only as Hellspawn! Meanwhile, the mysterious Snakeroot finally makes its move!
description.16: Hulk is on a mission to rescue an old friend from captivity. There's only one problem - her captor is none other than Nick Fury, and her prison is none other than S.H.I.E.L.D.!
description.17: From the pages of the X-Men-Iron Man battles the mutant villain, Omega Red!
description.20: Thor spirals out of control under the Dark Valkyrie's thrall. Will Asgard be burnt to the ground by its own prince?
description.22: Random stages an attack on Polaris! But what is the vigilante truly after? Havok attempts to get used to Forge's new position, while Rahne flies off the handle…again!
description.23: Shaman and Talisman do battle in the Goddess' ""sacred"" haven!
description.24: It's a rivalry that has spanned decades, and crossed dimensions! Now, Doctor Doom and Mr. Fantastic face off for a climactic duel to the death! But will Reed have to pay an unspeakable price to defeat his greatest foe?
description.26: Wolverine and Jubilee may have escaped the Sentinels, but Jubilee is still out for revenge. With help from an unexpected ally, can she finally find the people who killed her parents?
description.35: It all comes down to this! Against overwhelming numbers and odds, can the latest Secret Defenders possibly survive?
description.36: Working separately Wolverine and Punisher are both led to a case involving the Kingpin. The Kingpin has plans to ruin Frank's reputation, but can the two stop them before it's too late?
description.40: What if Death's Head I wasn't killed by Minion? It's a clash of two killer cyborgs in this cyberpunk tale from the 2020 timeline!
description.43: The origin of Daredevil is retold by legends Frank Miller and John Romita Jr.! What led Matt Murdock on the path to becoming the Man Without Fear?
description.47: Firestar has her work cut out for her against Asylum. Nova does what he must to defend the cosmos.
description.50: An Infinity Crusade tie-in! The Goddess comes to Luther Manning with an offer. Deathlok and Siege versus Timestream!
description.52: Sabretooth Vs. Wolverine! Mystique knows an awful lot about Sabretooth. What exactly has she been hiding from Logan?
description.54: A mystical healer is inadvertently placing damned souls in comatose patients. And Daimon Hellstrom won't stand for it! Runaways of hell… enjoy your final earthly hour.
description.59: Rampage of the Goliath Green Hulk! Spider-Man joins forces with Doc Samson to stop Hulk's attack in New York. Mary Jane's acting career hits the skids, while Aunt May vows to uncover the truth behind Peter's parents!
description.60: The Vision questions whether he can experience love the way his teammates do. While mulling over his past, Deathcry pushes Vision to an emotional breaking point. Is Vision truly the automaton he believes himself to be?
description.61: Revenge, thy name is SINSEAR! The mechanized killer from the future is out for blood, and he has Cable squarely in his sights! Can Nate survive the gauntlet of death that Sinsear has thrown him into? And what exactly is the reason for the cyborg's thirst for vengeance?
description.62: It's total mayhem as Captain America takes on the mysterious Blazing Skull!
description.63: The Lethal Legion are dispatched by Satannish to take down the Avengers West Coast. Their first target - U.S. Agent!
description.73: Daredevil's on the hunt for a mysterious man named Eddie, who's been sowing seeds of discord in the streets of New York. Unfortunately for him, Eddie's also the target of mercenaries led by Silver Sable! This is one showdown Matt Murdock won't be able to talk his way out of!
description.74: Madman, the King of England? Hulk must prevent his maniacal foe from carrying out a plot against Charles, Prince of Wales.
description.75: M.O.D.A.M. returns with a vengeance! M.O.D.A.M. obsessed with Tony Stark's demise seeks to have him killed at the hands of A.I.M. Will she succeed? We sure hope not!
description.77: Wolverine and the Punisher team up to defeat the Architect!
description.79: Thor vs. Drax the Destroyer! Odin recounts a past adventure of the Thunder God.
description.81: Havok and Polaris finally get their dinner date, but are interrupted by a bigoted mutant hater. Rahne struggles with her mutate state, while Forge embraces his role as a government liaison.
description.82: Tie-in to the Infinity Crusade! The team battles one of their own, until the Goddess intervenes.
description.83: At the perfect moment, Doctor Doom strikes! Baiting the Thing into chasing him alone, Doom quickly turns the tables and makes Ben Grimm his captive! But the rest of the Four are hot on his tail, and they're ready to lay siege to Castle Doom for as long as it takes to get Ben back!
description.85: Wolverine and Jubilee are… stuck in time?! The Sentinel pulls Wolverine and Jubilee into a time stream, and their chances at escape are pretty bleak…
description.95: Peter decides, once and for all, to find out what the deal is with these people who claim to be his parents- are they or aren't they? The aftermath of the Maximum Carnage crossover, this book features the work of the formidable Michelinie and Bagley creative team!
description.96: The Lunatic Legion triumphs over the Avengers! With the team either dispersed or kidnapped, Sersi's telepathic link is the only connection the team has. Who is the mysterious benefactor of Galen Kor? And what does he want with the Avengers?
description.97: Who will save Viper, leader of Hydra, when a hit has been placed on her head? Guest staring Silver Sable!

1.text: War is imminent on the planet Eopia due to the machinations of Mys-Tech unless the newly formed Dark Guard can stop it. But first, Death's Head and Motormorth must rescue Liger and Killpower from the Technarchy and Collapsar.

3.text: Bishop arrives from the future, does he come in peace?

4.text: After escaping the attackers from the Synge casino with the help of Bloodhawk, the X-men get to new hideout. But will the hideout be strong enough to hold off oncoming enemies?

7.text: Deadpool versus Makeshift and Rive!  Can Wade survive two deadly lady mercenaries at once?

8.text: Who is Thanatos? How did he achieve his warrior strength? And what beef does he have with Alchemax? Spider-Man 2099 meets a worthy opponent in battle, brawn, and fortitude! Jordan Boone finds himself in trouble yet again.

9.text: The Hangman has paid a big price for his power and he, along with the Lethal Legion, have targeted the Avengers West Coast for death!

11.text: After teaming up with Drax The Destroyer to fight Thor, The Hulk is abandoned and left to drift in space above Paradise Omega. Can the Jade Giant make it back to the surface in time to join the action?

After teaming up with Drax The Destroyer to fight Thor, The Hulk is abandoned and left to drift in space above Paradise Omega. Can the Jade Giant make it back to the surface in time to join the action?

22.text: Cyclops goes looking for his ex-wife and son only to find an old enemy!

27.text: The X-Men have gotten into some pretty intense scraps over the years, but few have escalated the way their battle with Magneto did in the "Fatal Attractions" storyline. If Mags ripping the adamantium off Wolverine's bones didn't end the fight, it was Professor X mind-wiping Magneto that did.

28.text: Tombstone is on the hunt! His first target -- Flash Thompson! Plus, a major change in the life of Peter Parker!

29.text: Storm and Wonder Man are controlled by Goddess!

30.text: Volstagg has always been one of Thor's closest friends but what happens when he has a "mostly" great adventure of his own? (Note: this issue contains only the Volstagg story)

31.text: Will Mistress of Time Terminatrix rely on the Avengers when she gets in over her head? Cap, Iron Man, and Thor battle it out with the men who once assumed their identities! Chronopolis rumbles as two time-warped Avengers teams assemble!

33.text: This is Luke Cage as you’ve never seen him before – under possession by the Bogeyman! Unleashed and raving, Cage goes on a bender.

34.text: The Guardians discover that Loki has brainwashed the Inhuman people!

35.text: It all comes down to this! Against overwhelming numbers and odds, can the latest Secret Defenders possibly survive?

36.text: Working separately Wolverine and Punisher are both led to a case involving the Kingpin. The Kingpin has plans to ruin Frank's reputation, but can the two stop them before it's too late?

37.text: Timothy Fitzgerald meets Xi'an Chi Xanh, a man who preaches about equality. However, a man is found dead in a way that resembles Xi'an's mutant powers. Will Fitzgerald be able to help out his new friend?

38.text: X-Force takes it upon themselves to save Gyrich- despite the wishes of Val Cooper, Nick Fury, and Professor X! Reignfire gives Cable an ultimatum- join his team or die!

41.text: Kismet’s cocoon is delivered to Project: Pegasus courtesy of Quasar and Kayla!

42.text: A battle arises over the death of Pura-Shamutra! Doctor Strange vs. Urthona!

45.text: Venom and Punisher team up to kill a gang who murdered someone purely as an initiation right.

46.text: Spider-Man has his back to the wall against this onslaught of foes! Doc Ock, Vulture, Rhino, and more are all determined to send Peter to a world of pain!

48.text: Will the titanic trio of future Thor Dargo Ktor, Beta-Ray Bill and Thunderstrike, put their differences aside in time to knock Zarrko the Tomorrow Man into next week?

49.text: Sam Buchanan has faced all manner of horrific fiends and tormentors…but he has yet to encounter the likes of the barbaric Monstrosity!

51.text: Faustus convinces Jack to assassinate the Slug…can Cap stop his friend from committing murder?

53.text: Dark Guard is formed by The Time Guardian to defeat Mys-Tech before they subjugate all mankind.

55.text: The X-Men face a challenge greater than ever before!

56.text: What is the R-Gang of 2099, and what will they do to cause mischief? (Note: this issue does not contain the Hulk 2099 story in the original print version.)

57.text: The X-Men encounter a dangerous “energy thief” by the name of Jonathan Chambers. Is Chambers man or mutant? And what is the end-goal of his theft of mutant powers? The answer will surprise you! Revanche makes a devastating admission that will change her future with the X-Men.

58.text: Our Rebel heroes seek help from the Mon Calamari in evacuating their Yavin base, but soon get embroiled in a mystery involving a distress beacon of unknown origin, scads of Imperial troopers, giant sea worms, an amphibian rescue, more giant sea worms, a droid or two, a few more scads of Imperial troopers, and a bit more excitement that can't be contained!

63.text: The Lethal Legion are dispatched by Satannish to take down the Avengers West Coast. Their first target - U.S. Agent!

64.text: Magneto falls under the crosshairs of a dangerous assassin, a man called Adrian Eiskalt. Eiskalt blames Magneto for the death of his brother and will stop at nothing to destroy the Master of Magnetism.

66.text: Deadpool must get through Juggernaut and Black Tom Cassidy in order to secure a mysterious case that holds the secret of Tolliver's will.

67.text: When a vandal acts against criminal corporation Alchemax, the Public Eye will stop at nothing to teach a lesson! Enter Miguel O’ Hara to save the day. Will Spider-Man 2099 be able to outrun the technical weaponry of S.I.E.G.E.? And will Miguel and Dana get a much needed vacation?

69.text: Earth's gathered champions are rocketing toward Paradise Omega, home of Adam Warlock's virtuous female doppleganger, the Goddess. Has she been slain? What is next for the heroes?
Earth's gathered champions are rocketing toward Paradise Omega, home of Adam Warlock's virtuous female doppleganger, the Goddess. Has she been slain? What is next for the heroes?

70.text: Mephisto knows how to use the Cosmic Cubes in ways no one was meant to use them. His price for the information: a Cosmic Cube once the Goddess is defeated. His customers? Thanos and Adam Warlock!

77.text: Wolverine and the Punisher team up to defeat the Architect!

87.text: The Silver Surfer has become a living Cosmic Bomb!

89.text: Rictor faces heartbreak over Boomer, while Siryn behaves badly. At Whitman Maximum Security Prison, the new villain Reignfire has escaped…with a plan to kill Henry Gyrich!

93.text: In order for Urthona to acquire a device to rebuild his world, he teams up with Jarakk to battle Pura-Shamutra, a god fighting on the side of the Trinity of Ashes.

98.text: The sequel to ‘Citizen Kang’ guest-stars Thunderstrike, US Agent, and War Machine! Terminatrix attempts to expand Chronopolis beyond Kang's seven-millennium boundaries, and discovers a shocking secret about time!

99.text: Will the unbreakable Cage be able to resist psychic persuasion while battling the Homeless Killer?
